tips.text: Best dining experience - has the potential to be a top 10 restaurant in the world! Chef's 8 course + dessert is full of wonderful surprises, leaving you wanting more!
Amazing crab pasta, and the tiramisu is out of this world.
Excellent miso pumpkin rice with garlic & egg yolk. paella meets Japanese risotto. Cocktails are amazing. Highly recommend the kyoho fizz drink. Good place for dinner then drinks in the neighborhood.
Been here since I was a kid, gotta try the dai ha mai

BE Sanger (pulled pork, chipotle aioli - served in brioche bun): Ask 2 cut 'burger' in half- makes for a nice snack to share over cocktails. Aioli gave ea bite a mild play w d chilli & garlic flavours
Oysters are $2-3 apiece during happy hour – 5pm to 7pm every day, and all night on Mondays!
Must try the salt baked beetroot, w burrata & truffle honey, mini Spanish breakfast, and popcorn milk chocolate mousse! The short ribs and scallops were just okay. Arrive post 930 to avoid the wait.
Food is totally overpriced but drinks and atmosphere at bar upstairs are great, so have dinner somewhere else and come here only for drinks.
Went for lunch, fish was quite under seasoned while the veal was tender but lacking real depth of flavor. Dessert flan was way too sweet. Don't think we'll be back.
The buffet is really value for money. My Favourite is the brisket even though the fat content is so high. Eat with raw garlic and kimchi, chased with cold beer. It's so so good.

formattedAddress: 2 Teck Lim Road (Off Keong Saik Rd)

tips.text: Good value set lunch. Yummy food with even yummier desserts. Don't miss their lemon tart - One of those rare places that dares to let the tartness shines through. Love!
Beef rague papadelle aka beef pasta
What a great find. Feels like in Australia. Wholesome food with an easy vibe. For something light, don't miss the quinoa salad or the granola yogurt. For something heavier, try the smoked mackerel!
Thursday special! Corona for $2.50!
Very good dessert !

formattedAddress: 6 Keong Saik Road (cnr of Keong Saik & Jiak Chuan)
location.crossStreet: cnr of Keong Saik & Jiak Chuan

tips.text: Char siew here is grrreat!!! Thick juicy slices unlike the paper-thin, dry ones you get everywhere else in Singapore!
Generally good food and drinks. Great ambience too. Love the grilled corn on the cob and the blue corn cake dessert.
Squid Ink Tonnarelli is to die for!!!
Hazelnut panna cotta is heavenly. It like eating ferrero rocher in custard form. Must try !
Drinks time every Friday and Saturday night 10.30pm - 1am!
Reasonable price with good food. Nice to enjoy the mood of korea
Great bar - amazing ginger beer - get a seat in the dinning room at the bar

formattedAddress: 2 Duxton Hill, #01-01 (cnr Duxton Rd & Duxton Hill)

tips.text: Quite enjoyed the Earl Grey Choco. A nice, light dessert with nice hints of earl grey, chocolate and sliced banana in the middle.
Try the steaks on the menu, they are famous for that.
great place for brunch, desserts & a working lunch. staff keep on their smiley attitude even during a full house. never fails.
Try the tasting menu. Spicy octopus dish followed by slightly sweet duck was high gastronomy. Lively atmosphere with music and open kitchen.
Their food are very satisfying!! Definitely will go back again.
Awesome squid-ink pasta, gotta try it!
Dark chocolate banana is SUPER AWESOME!!! Choc is rich yet not too sweet or creamy, banana taste real. On softer side, tofu strawberry is more mild, combi of sour, sweet n smooth!
Superb Italian fare
Try the $39.50++ 3-course set lunch. See pics and review at http://sparklette.net/food/restaurant-ember/
Seriously one of the best Italian restaurants in this part of the world.
Fabulicious as always, with a special birthday cake some more... Yummmm
Save some space for the Pistachio Tiramisu! Much better than the Lava Cake.
It is inaccurate of Andrea Kanya to say that there are vegan cakes available because their cakes do use dairy products such as cheese and butter. You can see that on their website and Facebook page.
Definitely top5 for proper coffee in town!
Absolutely delicious  !! Had the Black spicy tonkotsu special.  Ramen had perfect texture, eggs were nice and gooey in the middle, broth was tasty.  Even better with ground sesame.
The cheese selection is phenomenal. Nice place to reminisce summer in Paris!
the chairs are too high and tables are too low.
Excellent sushi and great service. Trust the chef, it will be delicious. 🍣

Amazing Concept! An Izakaya-ModernTapas Bar with a suprising menu changing everyday. Tasted Gurnard Tartar with Quinoa&Tofu and Kampong Egg with Baby Satong and Chorizo. Awesome flavours and textures!
Great food here. Get the crispy tofu, salted egg ribs, garlic chives and braised crab beehoon. $10 corkage fee for as many bottles of wine as you like!
uob card get 10% discount , no more 10% off for foursquare check-in, and use wifi by check-in facebook :-) bakeries are average, too light coffee C
would go back again for the delectable crab croquettes &, shakshouka. I'd also recommend the Merlot by the glass or Malbec. lovely service & ambience. make sure to book!
The seasoned meat are tasty as compared to the grilled ones. They used traditional charcoal for barbecuing.
Waffle with Greek yoghurt and fruits is world best!
We enjoyed great service, delicious food and generous portions. The array of mozzarella on offer to start should not be missed, especially the burrata. Save some room for a sensational tiramisu!
Grilled fig and goat cheese bruschetta is good!
Love the Vintage decor. Try the Ungai Benedict for Brunch.
